Bro ab clear ho gaya issue database side me hai ✅

web.log me PostgreSQL migration/database error aa raha hai.

Most probably:

DB permission issue
old corrupted DB
Sonar schema create nahi hua properly

Ab clean fix karte hain.

Step 1 — Stop SonarQube
sudo systemctl stop sonarqube
Step 2 — Login PostgreSQL
sudo -u postgres psql
Step 3 — Delete Old Database

Inside psql run:

DROP DATABASE sonarqube;
DROP USER sonar;
Step 4 — Create Fresh DB + User
CREATE DATABASE sonarqube;
CREATE USER sonar WITH ENCRYPTED PASSWORD 'sonar123';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE sonarqube TO sonar;
ALTER DATABASE sonarqube OWNER TO sonar;

Exit:

\q
Step 5 — Give Schema Permissions

Run:

sudo -u postgres psql -d sonarqube

Then:

GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA public TO sonar;
ALTER SCHEMA public OWNER TO sonar;

Exit:

\q
Step 6 — Start SonarQube Again
sudo systemctl restart sonarqube

Wait 1 minute.

Step 7 — Check Logs
tail -f /opt/sonarqube/logs/web.log

If you see:

SonarQube is operational

Then open:

http://13.233.161.170:9000
Step 8 — Verify Port
sudo ss -tulnp | grep 9000

